727234f-a.title: Queens: Liberty Avenue - 171st Street
727234f-a.text:
(1)
Liberty Avenue, north side, east frow near 171st Street,
showing sowe very old houses, rewains of the past. This part
of Liberty Avenue was formerly South Street and one of the
Main east-west thoroughfares of Jawaica Village.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(2)
No. 172-15 Liberty Avenue, the twin-chiwneyed house seen
in view 1.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(3)
A clearance next to the old house seen in view 2, and be-
tween the house and the one-story brick garage seen in view 1.
The olearance extends north to Douglas Avenue and shows an
old dwelling on the north side of the latter avenue. Behind
the house is the steel elevated structure of the Long IIsland
Railroad.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
